  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part">
<p>
	A <b>Part</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>
	that collects the definitional information of the versions of  either a 
	<module_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:3_definition">part</module_ref> 
	or of a 
	<module_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:3_definition">non-countable material</module_ref>.
</p>
	<note number="1">A <b>Part</b> does not represent an actual physical object that is or was existing in the real world.</note>
	<note number="2">
		A complex instance of the <b>Part</b> entity and of the 
		<express_ref linkend="Document_and_version_identification:arm:Document_and_version_identification_arm.Document">Document</express_ref> 
		entity may be created in order to represent a document that is a component of a manufactured product, for example a user manual of a car.
	</note>
<p>
	A <b>Part</b> may be further characterised by a 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_related_product_category"/> 
	with the 
	<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_category.name"/> 
	"discrete" for a discrete part or "not-discrete" for a non discrete part.
</p>
	<note number="3">
		In the absence of a 
		<express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_related_product_category"/>
		with  "discrete" or "not-discrete" a post-processor may assume "discrete".
		
	</note>
	</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part  Where: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part.wr:WR1">
   The <b>Part</b> shall belong to a product category named 'part', 'raw material' or 'tool'.
   </ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part  Where: IP1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part.wr:IP1">
<p>If the <b>Part</b> represents a non-countable material that is used as a component in an assembly, the <b>Part</b> shall be, in addition, referred to by a <express_ref linkend="product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product_category_assignment"/>

 and the associated category shall have the name 'non-countable material'.</p>
<note number="3">This association is needed for a correct determination of the respective quantity of the components of the assembly.</note>
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part_version
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version">
A <b>Part_version</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>

 that identifies a version of a part.  A <b>Part_version</b> serves as the collector
 of the data characterizing a realizable object in various  application contexts. 
<note>A <b>Part_version</b> is expected to be functionally and physically interchangeable with the other versions of the same <express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part"/>.</note>
   </ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_and_version_identification_arm  Entity: Part_version  Attribute: of_product
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version.of_product">
	the <express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part"/>

 of which the <b>Part_version</b> specifies a version.
   </ext_description>
   <ext_description 
       linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.part_version_constraint">Every <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> referencing a <express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part"/>

 is a <express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version"/>.
</ext_description>
   <ext_description 
       linkend="Part_and_version_identification_arm.part_version_constraint.wr:WR1">Every <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> referencing a <express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part"/>

 is a <express_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:arm:Part_and_version_identification_arm.Part_version"/>.
</ext_description>

